The paper deals with capacity regions of multiple access channels, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and communication complexity (cs.CC) sub-fields. The use of input and state constraints suggests a possible connection to signal processing and control theory (cs.SI), while the mention of a missing piece in a previous characterization points to a potential contribution to the multimedia (cs.MM) or networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-fields.
